-- Australia & NZ shares slip on weak commodity prices, Greece
-- 
-- Tue Dec 30, 2014 12:23AM EST
-- None



SYDNEY, Dec 30 (Reuters) - Australian and New Zealand shares retreated on Tuesday as falling commodity prices and political uncertainty in Greece made investors avoid risk.

The S&P/ASX 200 index <.AXJO>, which gained 1.5 percent on Monday,  slipped 1 percent to 5,416.600 at the close of trade, pulling back from a seven-week peak of 5,486.7. For the year, the benchmark was up 1.2 percent. On Tuesday, technology and energy sectors suffered the most, with losses of nearly 2 percent. Financials and miners slipped around 1 percent.